sources: ['US20010018170A1', '0206', '876 g of behenic acid (Edenor C22-85R, trade name, manufactured by Henkel Co.), 4230 ml of distilled water, 492 ml of a 5 N aqueous solution of NaOH, and 1200 ml of tert-butyl alcohol were mixed and allowed to react by stirring at 75.
